  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Derivatives Trading Executive (Entry-Level)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Derivatives Trading Executive -</strong></p><p> Entry-level</p><ul><li>Execute derivatives and forward/future contracts and/or other financial products trading instructions.</li><li>Collect and organize information related to assigned product and establish database to evaluate the market fundamentally and technically by following up supply, demand, global/regional geo-political developments and market dynamics.</li><li>Conduct research, analysis, and prepare regular reports on assigned products on daily and weekly basis to develop position-taking strategies on key markets.</li><li>Maintain real-time trading portfolio position to facilitate contracts pricing and portfolio valuation.</li><li>Reconcile executed derivatives trades with broker statements and confirmations on daily basis.</li><li>Maintain accurate reporting of derivative transactions and results.</li><li>Monitor margin calls/excess cash related to derivatives and work with finance team to optimize positions across brokers to minimize cash utilization.</li><li>Leverage AI tools and Large Language Models (LLMs) to enhance algorithmic trading, automated trade execution, market analysis, strategy development, and backtesting.</li><li>Handling reports and performing assistant functions</li><li>Participate company internal meeting, oversea training and undertake other ad-hoc tasks as assigned.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum Bachelor degree in finance, economics, math or a related field</li><li>Possesses strong interest in financial markets.</li><li>Eagerness to learn and adapt in a fast-paced, team-oriented environment.</li><li>Basic knowledge of futures and options.</li></ul><p><strong>Why Join Us?</strong></p><ul><li>Work with experienced traders and gain exposure to live markets.</li><li>Opportunity to apply cutting-edge AI tools in a trading environment.</li><li>Clear career development path with structured training and mentorship.</li><li>Dynamic, collaborative, and innovative culture.</li></ul>",
